      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "### Management Cluster Capacity Planning\n\nWeekly capacity review dashboard for management clusters. Shows HCP density, resource commitment ratios, and actual utilization for all MGMT clusters in a region.\n\n**Sections:**\n- **HCP Density** — current HCP count, % of 60-HCP ceiling, 7-day trend\n- **Node Resource Commitment** — CPU/memory commitment ratios (SVC + HCP combined), node counts\n- **Resource Utilization** — actual CPU/memory usage vs allocatable, top nodes\n\n**Datasources:**\n- **SVC AMW** (`Managed_Prometheus_services-*`) — node metrics, resource requests, allocatable capacity.\n- **HCP AMW** (`Managed_Prometheus_hcps-*`) — HCP density panels and HCP resource requests (ocm-* namespace metrics are routed here).\n\n**Notes:**\n- The 60-HCP-per-MGMT-cluster ceiling comes from ClusterSizingConfiguration.\n- HCP count = count of distinct `ocm-*` namespaces (via `kube_pod_info`).\n- Commitment ratios combine requests from both SVC and HCP workloads via SSE expressions.\n- Select \"All\" in the Cluster dropdown to compare all MGMT clusters in the region.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.6.9",
      "title": "Dashboard Info",
      "type": "text"
    },
